@PegasusWang Python 3 should _not_ encode `str` to `bytes`. We cannot guess what encoding you might want, and guessing just leads to _really_ subtle bugs where you send a request you think is valid, get weird 400 errors, and then spend hours of your time and ours trying to work out why and it turns out it's because Requests defaulted to using UTF-8 and your server was expecting Latin-1. You, the user, are responsible for emitting bytes from your generator.

